Review_body:
I really enjoyed the aesthetics of this film. The good things about bond's are it makes boring political and financial troubles exciting (in this one solar energy).Roger is consistent again, 2nd one as bond and he's going from strength to strength.Negatives from the film;
Third nips are horrible
Nik Nack is a little irritatingPositives from the film;
There are some very attractive women in this film who have great abdomens i.e the Belly dancer and Miss Goodnight in her bikini. Britt Ekland is stunning in this film.
Considering I hated JW Pepper in the last film I actually thought how he appeared in a cameo role this time was great. He's growing on me worryingly!
Hip and the girls karate moves are slick and the young Asian kid trying to sell the elephant is a good comedic scene. 'bloody tourist'Interesting points;
I noticed a goof in the film. The gangster at the start cocked his gun when in the funhouse and then again when he saw scaramanga. It was also interesting to see James Cossins who I recognised from Fawlty Towers.Good ending as it went full circle in the funhouse and this time Scaramanga is outwitted by his own bond dummy. This film deserves more praise.
